      {
        "content": "Social media, while connecting people globally, often contributes to mental health issues like anxiety, depression, and loneliness due to its design. Features such as infinite scrolling, algorithm-driven content, and social comparison mechanisms are engineered to maximize user engagement, often at the cost of mental well-being. These platforms can exacerbate feelings of inadequacy and isolation, particularly among vulnerable populations like teenagers. By reforming these exploitative designs\u2014prioritizing user mental health over engagement metrics\u2014social media can become a healthier space, reducing its negative psychological impacts and fostering genuine connections rather than superficial interactions.",
        "additional_kwargs": {
          "refusal": null
