      {
        "content": "Social media companies frequently exploit user data for profit, often without informed consent, violating fundamental privacy rights. They collect vast amounts of personal information\u2014ranging from location data to browsing habits\u2014under opaque terms, which are then sold or shared with third parties for targeted advertising and other purposes. This practice not only risks data breaches but also undermines individual autonomy over personal information. Strict regulation is necessary to ensure transparent data handling practices, enabling users to have control over their personal information and protecting them from potential misuse or exploitation by corporations prioritizing profit over privacy.",
