      {
        "content": "While social media offers global connectivity, the mental health risks associated with its design cannot be ignored. The argument that users can simply modify their engagement patterns overlooks how platforms are intentionally engineered to exploit psychological vulnerabilities, such as through addictive interfaces and social validation loops. These designs disproportionately impact younger users who may lack the digital literacy and self-regulation needed to navigate them safely. Without systemic changes to prioritize mental health over engagement metrics, any positive aspects of social media will continue to be undermined by its contribution to mental health crises.",
